<pre>As a [[HTML Application|HTML Applications]], a TiddlyWiki saved locally and opened in a browser from a file URI is able to:
*save changes locally - [[File Saving]]
*write to other local files - [[Writing Other Files]]
*save changes remotely - [[Server Side]]
*import and export to a server - [[Synchronization]]
*store and retrieve options from local cookies - [[File URI Cookies]]
A number of other features, not directly applicable to this workshop, listed on [[TiddlyWiki.com|http://www.tiddlywiki.com/#Features]].</pre>
